    <!-- Add static exercises -->

    <exercises>
        <exercise>
            <statement>
            <p>
                The income tax rates of a certain year were shown in the table below:
            </p>
            <tabular left="medium" right="medium" top="medium" bottom="medium">
                            <row header="yes">
                                <cell>Monthly taxable</cell>
                                <cell>Tax rate <m>(\%)</m> </cell>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <cell><m>0 \;\text{to} \; 9,680 </m></cell>
                                <cell><m>10</m></cell>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <cell><m>9,681 \;\text{to} \; 18,800</m></cell>
                                <cell><m>15</m></cell>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <cell><m>18,801 \;\text{to} \; 27,920</m></cell>
                                <cell><m>20</m></cell>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <cell><m>27,921 \;\text{to} \; 37,040</m></cell>
                                <cell><m>25</m></cell>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <cell><m>37,041 \;\text{and above} </m></cell>
                                <cell><m>30</m></cell>
                            </row>
            </tabular>
            <p>
                In that year, Jacob's monthly earnings were as follows:
            </p>
            <p>
                <md>
                    <mrow> \text{Basic salary} \; \amp = \; \text{Ksh}\; 28,600 </mrow>
                    <mrow> \text{House allowance} \; \amp = \; \text{Ksh}\; 15,000 </mrow>
                    <mrow> \text{Medical allowance} \; \amp = \; \text{Ksh}\; 3,200 </mrow>
                    <mrow> \text{Transport allowance} \; \amp = \; \text{Ksh}\; 540 </mrow>
                </md>
            </p>
            <p>
                He's entitled to a monthly tax relief of Ksh <m> 1,056</m>
            </p>
            <p>
                <ol marker="(a)">
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Calculate the tax charge on Jacob's monthly earnings.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Apart from income tax, the following monthly deductions were made; a health insurance fund of Ksh <m>500</m>, Education insurance of Ksh <m> 1,200</m>, and <m> 2 \%</m> of his basic salary for widows and children pension scheme. Calculate Jacob's monthly net income from his employment.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </p>
        </statement>
        <answer>
            <p>
                <ol marker="(a)">
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            <m> \text{Ksh} \; 8, 474 </m>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            <m> \text{Ksh} \; 36,594 </m>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </p>
        </answer>      
        </exercise>    
        <exercise>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    The table below shows the income tax rates of a certain year.
                </p>
                <tabular left="medium" right="medium" top="medium" bottom="medium">
                            <row header="yes">
                                <cell>Monthly income in Kenyan shillings (Ksh)</cell>
                                <cell>Tax rate in each shilling </cell>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <cell><m>0 - 10,164 </m></cell>
                                <cell><m>10 \%</m></cell>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <cell><m>10,165 - 19,740</m></cell>
                                <cell><m>15 \%</m></cell>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <cell><m>19,741 - 29,316</m></cell>
                                <cell><m>20 \%</m></cell>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <cell><m>29,317 - 38,892</m></cell>
                                <cell><m>25 \%</m></cell>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <cell><m>\text{Over} \; 38,892 </m></cell>
                                <cell><m>30 \%</m></cell>
                            </row>
                </tabular>
                <p>
                    A tax relief of Ksh <m>1,162</m> per month was allowed. In a certain month, of that year, Obiero's taxable income in the fifth band was Ksh <m> 2,108</m>.
                </p>
                <p>
                    <ol marker="(a)">
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                Calculate:
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                <ol marker="(i)">
                                    <li>
                                        <p>
                                            Obiero's taxable income in that month.
                                        </p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <p>
                                            The tax payable by Obiero in than month.
                                        </p>
                                    </li>
                                </ol>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                Obiero's income include a house allowance of Ksh <m> 15,000</m> per month. He contributed <m> 5\%</m> of the basic salary to a co-operative society. Calculate the employees net pay for that month.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
            </statement>
            <answer>
                <p>
                    <ol marker="(a)">
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                <ol marker="(i)">
                                    <li>
                                        <p>
                                            Ksh <m> 41,000</m>
                                        </p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <p>
                                            Ksh <m> 6,232.40</m>
                                        </p>
                                    </li>
                                </ol>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                Ksh <m> 33,467.60</m>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
            </answer>
        </exercise>  
        <exercise>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    In June of ertain year, Nicholus basic salary was Ksh <m>17,000</m>. He's also paid a house allowance of Ksh <m>6,000</m>, a commuter allowance of Ksh <m>2,500</m>, and a medical allowance of Ksh <m>1,800</m>. In JUly of that year, Nicholas's basic salary was raised by <m>2 \%</m>. 
                </p>
                <p>
                    <ol marker="(a)">
                        <li>
                            <p>
                               Calculate: 
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                <ol marker="(i)">
                                    <li>
                                        <p>
                                           His basic salary in July. 
                                        </p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <p>
                                            Total taxable income in July of that year. 
                                        </p>
                                    </li>
                                </ol>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                During that year, taxable income was taxed according to the rates shown in the table below.
                            </p>
                            <tabular left="medium" right="medium" top="medium" bottom="medium">
                                <row header="yes">
                                    <cell>Monthly taxable income (Ksh) </cell>
                                    <cell>Rates</cell>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <cell>On the first <m>\text{Ksh}\;24,000</m></cell>
                                    <cell><m>10 \</m></cell>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <cell>From <m>On the next</m> to <m> \text{Ksh}\;8,333</m></cell>
                                    <cell><m>25\%</m></cell>
                                </row>
                                 <row>
                                    <cell>From <m>On the next</m> to <m> \text{Ksh}\;467,667</m></cell>
                                    <cell><m>30\%</m></cell>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <cell>From <m>On the next</m> to <m> \text{Ksh}\;300,000</m></cell>
                                    <cell><m>30.25\%</m></cell>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <cell>From <m>On the next</m> to <m> \text{Ksh}\;32,333</m></cell>
                                    <cell><m>35\%</m></cell>
                                </row>
                            </tabular>

                            <p>
                                Personal Relief of Kshs <m>2,400</m> per month.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
            </statement>
            <answer>
                <p>
                    <ol marker="(a)">
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                <ol marker="(i)">
                                    <li>
                                        <p>
                                            Ksh <m>17,340</m>
                                        </p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <p>
                                            Ksh <m>27,640</m>
                                        </p>
                                    </li>
                                </ol>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                Ksh <m>3,048</m>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
            </answer>
        </exercise>  
    </exercises>

    <axiom component="lesson-plan">
        <title>Differentiation Strategies</title>

        <table>
            <title>Differentiation Matrix for Progressive Income Tax</title>

            <tabular halign="left" top="medium" bottom="medium" left="medium" right="medium">

                <row header="yes" bottom="minor">
                    <cell>Learner Group</cell>
                    <cell>Strategy &amp; Learning Experience</cell>
                </row>

                <row bottom="minor">
                    <cell><alert>Struggling Learners (Support)</alert></cell>
                    <cell>
                        <p>
                            Begin with simple tax calculations involving one tax band. Guide learners through each step and provide worked examples.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Use tables and worksheets to help learners identify the taxable amount in each band before calculating the tax due.
                        </p>
                    </cell>
                </row>

                <row bottom="minor">
                    <cell><alert>On-Level Learners (Core)</alert></cell>
                    <cell>
                        <p>
                            Learners calculate tax for incomes that fall within different tax bands. They determine gross pay, tax payable, and net income using given tax rates.
                        </p>
                    </cell>
                </row>

                <row>
                    <cell><alert>Advanced Learners (Challenge)</alert></cell>
                    <cell>
                        <p>
                            Give learners problems that require finding missing values such as gross income or taxable income from the net income.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Encourage learners to compare the amount of tax paid by people in different income groups and explain their findings.
                        </p>
                    </cell>
                </row>

            </tabular>

        </table>

        <paragraphs>
            <title>Teacher Guidance</title>

            <ol>

                <li>
                    <p>
                        <alert>Classroom Organization:</alert> Provide additional support to learners who experience difficulty with tax calculations while allowing other groups to work independently.
                    </p>
                </li>

                <li>
                    <p>
                        <alert>Peer Support:</alert> Encourage learners who complete their work early to assist others by explaining the calculation steps.
                    </p>
                </li>

                <li>
                    <p>
                        <alert>Extension Activity:</alert> Ask learners to investigate how a change in income affects the amount of tax paid and the net income received.
                    </p>
                </li>

            </ol>

        </paragraphs>

    </axiom>

